<p><b>Glen David Brin</b>, Ph.D. (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1950-10-06"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="10-06"><a href="/wiki/October_6" title="October 6">October 6</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1950" title="1950">1950</a></span>) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> scientist and award-winning author of <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a>. He has received the <a href="/wiki/Hugo_award" title="Hugo award" class="mw-redirect">Hugo</a> <sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>, Locus <sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> <sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> <sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3" title=""><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup>, <a href="/wiki/Campbell" title="Campbell">Campbell</a> <sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4" title=""><span>[</span>5<span>]</span></a></sup>, and <a href="/wiki/Nebula_Award" title="Nebula Award">Nebula Awards</a> <sup id="cite_ref-5" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-5" title=""><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup>.</p>
